The Pope is at the summit of the one, the king at the summit of the other. As spiritual is superior to secular power, as to antiquity‚ dignity‚ and usefulness‚ it came to pass that in the beginning the psople of Israel was governed only by the spiritual power.

This division may be objected to, because one and the same person may wield both powers: as in the case of Melchisedech. Again, under the New Covenant‚ the clergy has aspired to temporal dominion; and lastly it is the King’s duty to uproot the vices of the clergy: which is tantamount to spiritual power. We must, therefore, seek for a better definition: Spiritual Power is the power of the Spirit, under whose immediate guidance man is led to follow God’s grace.
